At least 21 miners had been confirmed dead by Monday afternoon from a gas explosion took place Sunday in a coal mine in northeast China's Liaoning Province. According to local officials, the explosion occurred around 7: 30 p.m. in the Mengjiagou(also named Majiazi) Coal Mine in Fushun City. Among the 45 miners who were working in the mine at the time of the accident, 21 have managed to escape while three others remained missing. The cause of the accident is under investigation and operation of another 23 local small coal mines has been suspended. Enditem 